  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Qpop is a customer-facing application designed to enhance interaction and engagement at the point of sale through a dedicated touchscreen device (tablet). Always facing the customer, Qpop allows for seamless interaction during the sales process by:</p><ul><li><p>Displaying in-store advertisements and promotions</p></li><li><p>Showing real-time ticket details for customer review</p></li><li><p>Presenting electronic forms and waivers for acknowledgment</p></li><li><p>Capturing electronic signatures for payments via integrated devices</p></li></ul><p>As a browser-based solution, Qpop eliminates the need for expensive proprietary hardware. Simply choose your preferred tablet or touchscreen device, pair it with your location, and start engaging with your customers!</p><h3 id=\"CreateaQpop\u2122Companion-NextSteps\">Next Steps</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936490516/Pair+a+Qpop+Companion\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936490516\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Pair a Qpop Companion</a></p></li></ul><h3 id=\"CreateaQpop\u2122Companion-OptionalFeaturesandAdditionalResources\">Optional Features and Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936949331/Send+Custom+Forms+to+Your+Qpop+Companion+Device\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936949331\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Send Custom Forms to Qpop\u2122 Companion</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936359503/Capture+Integrated+Payment+Signatures+on+a+Qpop+Companion\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936359503\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Capture Integrated Payment Signatures on a Qpop Companion</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1937047567/Qpop+Companion+Resources+with+Video\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1937047567\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936523288/Qpop+Companion+System+Requirements\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936523288\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion System Requirements</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936654410/Qpop+Companion+Troubleshooting\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936654410\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion Troubleshooting</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-175947.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"CreateaQpop\u2122Companion-AddaQpop\u2122CompaniontoRepairQ\">Add a Qpop\u2122 Companion to RepairQ</h2><p>Log into your RepairQ location on your computer. On the RepairQ Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Location Settings</strong>. On the Settings Overview page, the left column lists different settings categories. Click on <strong>Qpop</strong> to expand the options and select <strong>Qpop Companions</strong>.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Users with the Shift Lead role or higher can pair and launch Qpop.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-175953.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"253\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-175959.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"CreateaQpop\u2122Companion-CreateaNewCompanion\">Create a New Companion</h3><p>On the Qpop Companions page, click <strong>Set up a Qpop Companion</strong>. Give your companion a name (without any special characters). Select the location where this companion will be used, and enter a description to add any specific details about this device.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-180004.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-180010.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>If you would like to add your own images to your Qpop Companion, click the <strong>Idle Screen Image</strong>\u00a0to edit the image that will show on the companion when idle.\u00a0</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-180015.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"CreateaQpop\u2122Companion-AddImagestoYourDevice\">Add Images to Your Device</h3><p>Drag and drop images from your computer to the <strong>Image Upload Box</strong> for graphics that you wish to upload. You can also click the box to browse files on your computer. For best results, see <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://repairq.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/115005569288\" rel=\"nofollow\">Qpop\u2122 Companion - Recommended Image Resolutions</a> for sizing your images correctly.</p><p>When you upload an image, the preview will show on the companion screen in RepairQ.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-180022.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Alternatively, you can also click <strong>Add from library</strong> to select an image that has been previously uploaded to your Qpop Image Library. The Idle-Screen pop-up will allow you to select an image with a preview. Click Add Image to assign the image to your Qpop Companion.</p><p><strong>Note:\u00a0</strong>You can upload up to five images which will cycle when Qpop is idle.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-180027.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Click the <strong>Ticket Summary Image</strong> to edit the image that will show when you are viewing a ticket.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-180033.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Drag and drop images from your computer to the <strong>Image Upload Box</strong> for graphics that you wish to upload. You can also <strong>click the box to browse files</strong> on your computer or click <strong>Add from library</strong> to select a previously uploaded image. When you select an image, the preview will show on the companion screen in RepairQ.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Qpop 8.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/Qpop%208.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Once satisfied with your changes, click <strong>Save</strong> to finish creating your companion. Your companion device will show on the device list. If you need to change the settings for your Companion, you can click the <strong>Edit</strong> button to make any changes to your device's name, assignment, or images, and be sure to save after changes.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1937014846/image-20230608-180057.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
